comments: Williams (OKC) moves alongside James' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Williams (OKC) legally contests James' (LAL) driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) legally contests James' (LAL) driving shot attempt at the basket.
Williams (OKC) establishes himself in Brown Jr.'s (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Westbrook (LAL) legally contests Giddey's (OKC) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) brushes Davis' (LAL) arm as he attempts to secure the rebound and the contact is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) reaches in and makes contact to Beverly's (LAL) arm and affects his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Williams (OKC) avoids making contact with Westbrook (LAL) during his contest of the layup attempt at the basket.
Brown Jr. (LAL) moves to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) space and marginal contact occurs prior to the pass.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Williams' (OKC) perimeter shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) and Brown Jr. (LAL) simultaneously come into contact with the ball and incidental arm and body contact occurs.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) legally contests Westbrook's (LAL) layup attempt at the basket.
Muscala (OKC) establishes himself in Davis' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the players come together during the screen.
Davis (LAL) brings his arm around Giddey (OKC) and marginal arm contact occurs at the start of Giddey's drive.
Brown Jr. (LAL) legally deflects Giddey's (OKC) pass after the release.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) extends his hand forward and initiates contact with Westbrook's (LAL) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) briefly clamps Muscala's (OKC) arm and releases while rebounding.
Brown Jr. (LAL) and Giddey (OKC) bring their hands to the ball simultaneously and incidental contact occurs during the rebound.

Westbrook (LAL) brings his hand to the ball and part of Giddey's (OKC) hand that is on the ball, which dislodges it during the rebounding opportunity. Giddey proceeds to lose his balance and fall to the floor after the dislodge.
Westbrook (LAL) initiates arm contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC), which affects his ability to secure the loose ball.
Joe (OKC) goes to the ground on his own accord and avoids making contact with Beverley (LAL).
Giddey (OKC) legally contests Schroder's (LAL) perimeter shot attempt.

Replay review of the loose ball foul called on Beverley (LAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Beverley makes contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it from Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
OKC should have been awarded the ball following the successful challenge since Williams (OKC) had imminent possession at the point of interruption, which occurred after the ball was dislodged.
Prior to any contact with the ball, Williams (OKC) jumps from point A to point B and initiates body contact with Westbrook (LAL) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) commits a take foul on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
Brown Jr. (LAL) and Williams (OKC) come together during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Beverley (LAL) commits a take foul on Williams (OKC). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Play is stopped due to a clock malfunction. After the correction, play resumes with Los Angeles retaining possession.
Westbrook (LAL) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes more than two steps prior to releasing his shot attempt.
Williams (LAL) brings his arm to a legal vertical position and legally contests Westbrook's (OKC) driving shot attempt.
Brown Jr. (LAL) brushes Williams' (OKC) arm and the contact during the dunk attempt at the basket is marginal.
Williams (OKC) legally contests Beverley's (LAL) perimeter shot attempt.
